STATE GOVERNMENT SUBSTITUTE TO HB69
OFFERED BY REPRESENTATIVE HAMMETT
1
2
3
4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a water well contractor is
6 required to be licensed by the Alabama Department of
7 Environmental Management.
8 This bill would further provide for an
9 unrestricted well driller's license and for a
10 restricted license for engaging in drilling specific
11 wells or pump installation, repair, and related
12 activity.
13 This bill would increase the fee for licensure
14 and provide for a two-year licensure period.
15 This bill would further require continuing
16 education of licensees.
17 This bill would also authorize the Environmental
18 Management Commission to adopt rules to implement this
19 act, including fees for filing water well completion
20 certifications.
21
22
23 A BILL
24 TO BE ENTITLED
25 AN ACT
26
27 Relating to the Alabama Department of Environmental
28 Management and well driller licenses; to amend Sections
