120 "§22-24-5
121 Every person who intends to drill water wells within
122 the State of Alabama shall annually obtain from the board a
123 water well driller's license and, in order to obtain said
124 license, shall file with the board, in accordance with rules
125 and regulations as established by the board, an application
126 form, to be made available by the board. Any person, upon
127 filing said application and receiving approval of the board,
128 shall pay an annual fee of $200.00 to the board, and the
129 payment of said fee shall entitle said person to the full and
130 complete privileges of drilling water wells, as provided in
131 this chapter, and the board shall issue a license for a period
132 not to exceed one year. Said annual fee paid to the board
133 shall not exempt a person from additional state or county
134 privilege taxes.(a) A person who manages or supervises the
135 drilling or repair of a water well, monitoring well,
136 geothermal well, or cathodic protection well; installs,
137 maintains, or repairs a pump; or performs any related activity
138 shall be licensed under this chapter.
139 (b) The department shall issue two types of licenses as
140 follows:
Page 5

follows:
141 (1) An Unrestricted Well Driller's License. A license
142 that authorizes a person to engage in the business of: (i)
143 drilling and repairing water wells, monitoring wells,
144 geothermal wells, and cathodic protection wells; (ii)
145 installing, maintaining, and repairing pumps; and (iii) any
146 related activity.
147 (2) A Restricted License. A license that authorizes a
148 person to engage in only one or more of the following
149 activities as specified in the conditions of the license:
150 a. Drilling of and related activity for a specific type
151 of well.
152 b. Installation, maintenance, and repair of pumps.
153 (c) A license may be issued to an individual or to a
154 business entity. A license may only be issued to a business
155 entity if a principal employee who is individually licensed is
156 listed on the business entity's license.
157 (d) Commencing October 1, 2026, all licenses issued by
158 the department shall be valid for a two-year license period.
159 (e)(1) The department shall charge a fee to issue a
160 license as follows:
161 a. An unrestricted license fee shall be one thousand
162 dollars ($1,000).
163 b. A restricted license fee shall be five hundred
164 dollars ($500).
165 (2) An additional fee of five hundred dollars ($500)
166 shall be charged for the issuance of a business license.
167 (f) A license shall be renewed on October 1 and shall
168 be delinquent if not paid by December 31 of each renewal
Page 6

be delinquent if not paid by December 31 of each renewal
169 period. Any renewal that is delinquent may be renewed by the
170 payment of an additional delinquency fee of twenty dollars
171 ($20) per month of delinquency, for up to one year.
172 (g) An applicant for an initial individual license
173 shall be subject to examination and shall satisfy all
174 requirements as provided by rule of the commission. The
175 license fee for a new licensee shall be prorated on a monthly
176 basis for the balance of the license period.
177 (h)(1) Commencing on the renewal of each license for
178 the license period beginning on October 1, 2028, each
179 individual licensee shall submit proof of completing eight
180 hours of continuing education approved by the department
181 according to license type to renew a license.
182 (2) A licensee who fails to submit proof of completing
183 the required continuing education shall be given a grace
184 period to complete the continuing education until March 31
185 after the commencement of the new license period."
