237 "§22-24-8
238 It shall be unlawful and a violation of this chapter to
239 drill a water well within the State of Alabama unless the
240 following provisions are complied with:(a) A licensee shall do
241 all of the following while performing an activity for which a
242 license is required by this chapter:
243 (1) The driller of the water well shall be licensed as
244 provided in Section 22-24-5.
245 (2)(1) The driller shall, at At all times during the
246 drilling of a water well, keep posted in a conspicuous
247 location, at or near the well being drilled or on his person,
248 the appropriate license certificate as furnished on the
249 drilling equipment a current sticker issued by the department
250 indicating licensure by the board.
251 (3)(2) Before the commencement of the drilling
252 operation starting the construction of a well, the driller
Page 9

operation starting the construction of a well, the driller
253 shall file an application of intent to drill a water well, as
254 directed by the board department.
255 (4)(3) The driller of the well, within Within 30 days
256 after completion of completing the drilling of each water a
257 well, shall deliver to the board department a well completion
258 certification form, upon forms to be supplied by the board, a
259 "report of well drilled.". The board department shall notify
260 the local health authorities within seven days of the receipt
261 thereof receiving the certification for potable and
262 agricultural water wells only.
263 (5)(4) The driller shall furnish Furnish a log and a
264 set of samples to the State Geological Survey from wells
265 specifically designated by the board department or State
266 Geologist. The samples shall be collected during the drilling
267 at intervals of not more than 10 feet.
268 (b) The commission, by rule, may adopt a schedule of
269 fees due for the filing of a well completion certification
270 form pursuant to subdivision (a)(3). A fee may not exceed one
271 thousand dollars ($1,000) and shall be in an amount according
272 to whether the well is used for an industrial, commercial, or
273 domestic purpose or other criteria as determined by rule of
274 the commission. The fee for a single-family residence or
275 duplex may not exceed two hundred fifty dollars ($250). The
276 fees may be paid electronically. All fees shall be deposited
277 into the Environmental Management Fund and used for the
278 administration of this chapter and shall not revert to the
279 State General Fund at the end of each fiscal year."
